extend ../templates/layout
block content
	h1 Public Shows
	p#intro The planetarium is open to the public for shows on Saturdays. Shows generally run about 1 hour. Seating capacity is 65 people/program.  Groups of ten or more are encouraged to make reservations in advance. For reservations, call 735-2148.
	h2 Upcoming shows:
	ul
		each upcomingShow in upcoming
			li
				h4= upcomingShow.title
				p= upcomingShow.description
				p.date Date and time: #{upcomingShow.date}
	//		
		li
			h4 Dawn of the Space Age
			p.aside Note: this program is suitable for those 8+ years old.
			p The program shows the beginning of our space exploration, and we finish with the future of space exploration.
			p.date Date and time: Saturday, October 15th at 1 pm.
	h2 Previous shows:
	ul
		each previousShow in previous
			li
				h4= previousShow.title
				p= previousShow.description
	//
		li
			h4 Natural Selection
			p We celebrate two great science thinkers born in February - Galileo and Darwin.
		li
			h4 Cool Stuff that Blows Up!
			p Exactly what it sounds like.
		li
			h4 Transit of Venus
			p How to view it, what you'll see, and how we use transits to prove the existence of other planets like Earth!
		li
			h4 Robots In Space!
			p
		li
			h4 Hubble - 20 Great Years!
			p The Hubble Space Telescope has changed how we see the universe and ourselves. Find out what we've learned and what we've yet to learn.  We will also take a 'sneak peak' at some brand new planetarium technology-the mirrordome projection system!  Come see yourself surrounded by space scenery!